text: [5/10/17] Draught at Himmeriget in Copenhagen. Black with a lovely brown head. Amazing aroma, chocolate, Nutella, vanilla, bourbon, roast, sweet, a bit boozy, full-bodied. Wonderful.

(On tap @ Himmeriget, Copenhagen, May 9/17) Pours black with a medium tan head and no lace. Aroma of rich chocolate, light maple, bourbon, vanilla, light coconut, hazelnut, nutty roast, a little fruit. Flavour is pretty rich up front, chocolate, fudge, moderate maple, vanilla, smooth whiskey, but becoming a fair bit more bitter with hazelnuts, nutty roast, wood, cacao, softly boozy, lingering bourbon tones. Finishes pretty dry for a stout with a dessert-loaded concept. Medium full body with very low carbonation. Tasty and far more drinkable than I expected.
On tap. Black color with tan head. Bourbon, toffee, dark chocolate, some fruits (dark cherries mostly), a hint of nuts on the finish. Medium body, quite boozy, medium carbonation.
Tap @ Himmeriget, Copenhagen. Pitch black pour with a dark tan head. Notes of sweet chocolate, hints of maple, coconut, light nutty with a light bitterness.
On tap at Himmeriget. Pitch black pour with a tan heah. Notes of bourbon, vanilla, chocolate, hazelnut, sour cherries, oak. Full body, bitter chocolatey cherry finish, with a light barrel sourness.
At Himmeriget, pours black with a beige head, aroma of chocolate, bourbon, toffee, lotus spread, flavor of chocolate, bourbon, toffee, Cinnamon, wood, coconut, full bodied

Tap @ Himmeriget, Copenhagen. Pours pitch black with a small dark brown head. Aromas of maple, Hazelnut, dark chocolate, light fudge, subtle acid notes. Taste is maple fudgey, vanilla, light roast, sweet toffee, dry cocoa acidity. Totally flat.
Tap na Warszawskim Festiwalu Piwa. Ohhh, jaki aromat. Syrop, wanilia, kokos, praliny, nuta kawy. Smak słodki, mamy tutaj podobnie jak w aromacie. Super piękne piwo, cieliste, aromatyczne i pyszne.
Tap na WFP. Bardzo intensywna beczka po bourbonie. Wanilia, kokos, jaki kokos, bounty w płynie, kawa, czekolada, orzechy, marcepan. Wspaniałe piwo.
Niesamowicie bogaty profil beczki po Bourbonie. Wanilia, opiekany kokos, szlachetny alkohol, słodka i wytrawna czekolada, orzechy, kawa, melasa. Znakomite piwo, klasa Cycle.

WFP 7.04.2017
Jest wszystko co obiecuje nazwa. Bardzo intensywne, z?o?one. G?ównie orzechy i beczka. ?wietne

Tap at Warszawski Festiwal Piwa. Aroma: Lots of chocolate, syrup, cocoa, vanilla, barrel. Appearance: Black body, almost no head. Taste: Sweet, full, cocoa, vanilla, barrel, bourbon, chocolate, maple syrup, very complex and intensive. Palate: Sweet finish, very high body, low carbonation.
WFP Backlog. Maple syrup, vanilla, hazelnut, chocolate, alcohol, oak. Great complexity but could be more intensive.
Po prostu pyszne. Jak ciasto czekoladowe, orzechowe z dodatkiem beczki i nasączone wanilią i bourbonem. Trochę mało ciała, ale i tak wspaniałe.

Tap at WFP. Black colour, small, quickly disappearing beige head. Very intense and complex aroma of maple syrup, bourbon, vanilla, some chocolate, coffee. Taste is medium to heavy sweet and medium bitter, of maple syrup, some chocolate, nuts, bourbon and alcohol. Bitter, boozy finish. Medium to full body, oily texture, soft carbonation. Aroma is amazing, but taste is slightly disappointing, a bit too boozy.

Kran WFP 17: czarne, prawie bez piany. W aromacie kakao, cola, kawa, troszke wanilii. W smaku polslodkie, delikatnie kwaskowe, czekoladowo colowo klonowe, wanilia w aftertejsie, malo ciala. Lekko destylatowe ala whisky. Dla mnie gorsze od podstawki.

Pite na Warszawskim Festiwalu Piwa. Nalało się z drobnym kręgiem drobnej brązowej piany, kolor głęboka czerń. W aromacie ogromna ilość czekolady, likieru orzechowego. W smaku mega słodkie, wyklejające, czuć ślady beczki, dużo procentowego trunku. Na gardle zostawia wrażenie rozgrzewania oraz mega słodyczy.

W aromacie sporo czekolady, kawy, orzechy, trochę beczki. W smaku czekoladowe, czuć nuty wanilii, mogłoby być więcej ciała. Naprawdę super piwo, ale chyba za bardzo się na nie nastawiłem i był lekki zawód.

Rami Rami is drinking an Imperial Biscotti Break Maple Bourbon Barrel Aged Chocolate Hazelnut by Evil Twin Brewing at Warszawski Festiwal Piwa

Zjednej strony czuc wszystko co w nazwie, z drugiej nie do konca takie to poukladane super. Ale nadal pyszne. Srednio z cialem.

Genialny aromat beczki. Wanilia bucha, bourbon równiez wyczuwalny. Czekolada, ciasteczka, praliny. Klasa. Piany brak, barwa czarna. W smaku mniej intensywnie ni? w aromacie. Jest s?odko, troch? owoców w czekoladzie czu?. Wanilia mocno wyczuwalna, czekoladowo, belgijskie czekoladki. Beczka przykry?a podstaw? majtórej g?ównie opiera? sie marcepan i migda?y. Wyklejaj?ce, troszku wiecej cia?ka by sie przyda?o. Waniliowy finisz, mniam. Alkohol lekko wyczuwalny. Ogólnie - petarda.

Draft @ Himmeriget, Copenhagen. Pours a black color with a small tan head. Has a roasted malty chocolate maple bourbon woody aroma. Roasted malty maple woody bourbon chocolate flavor with nutty hints. Has a roasted malty woody bourbon maple chocolate finish.
Evil Twin is always in top of their game and this stout is no exception. Wonderful thick head and extremely rich flavor. Definitely recommend this to all the Stout lovers out there.

Sweet and roasted malty with prominent notes of chocolate, interlaced with caramel and treacle sweetness, nice nutty notes, bourbon soaked wooden nuances with a caress of vanilla into the finish. Gorgeous.

From tap. Pours hazy dark brown to black with a small tan head. Aroma is dense malty, liqourice and smooth chocolate. Light vanilla. Sweet, dark malty. Lingering roasted and dark caramelish. Bitter and roasted dark malty finish.

Draught at Himmeriget.
Pitch black colored with a small beige head.
Roasted aroma of caramel, chocolate, licorice and bourbon.
Roasted flavor of caramel, chocolate, licorice and bourbon with notes of alcohol and port wine.
Roasted and warming alcoholic finish.

Draught at Himmeriget, Cph. Pitch black with no head. Sweet aroma with rich dark malts, chocolate, caramel, coffee and liquorice. Nuts. Soy sauce. Bourbon barrel, vanilla. Taste is sweet. Full body with an oily texture and a soft carbonation. Finishes lasting sweet with dark malts, lingering chocolate. Excellent, rich Porter.

How: Draught.
Where: All in Beerfest 2016.
Appearance: Black colour with a brown head.
Aroma: Chocolate, vanilla, bourbon, alcohol, hazelnuts.
Body: Full body, medium carbonation.
Flavour: Chocolate, bourbon, hazelnut, some coffee.

On tap @ Whats Brewing, Stavanger. Pours pitch black, with a small creamy head, off white head. Aroma is dark roasted malts, with bourbon barrels, tobacco, chocolate and coffee. Creamy body, with soft to average carbonation. Flavour is cocoa and bourbon barrels, tobacco, muscovado as well as coffee.

22.10.2016, tap @ Whats Brewing:
Nice light brown slightly fizzy-creamy mediumlasting head. Aroma is slightly rich and sweet boozy, dark malts, dark sugar, chocolate, minerals, bourbon, grass, nuts, caramel, chocolate pudding, oak, vanilla. Taste is slightly dry roasted, dark malts, dark sugar, chocolate, caramel, minerals, bourbon, grass, bark, vanilla, raisins, licorice, coffee, oak. Medium bitterness, slightly dry roasted and boozy mouthfeel. Nice.

Keg at Omnipollos Hatt, Stockholm.  Pitch black, rich beige head. Bourbon and hazelnuts up front. Very sweet with full body and dense, well rounded mouthfeel. Creamy milk chocolate, bourbon and nuts. Warming peppery finish. Harmonious, despite the onslaught of flavours.

On tap at Omnipollos Hatt. Pours black with a low mocha head. Aromas of dark chocolate, roasted malt, roasted hazelnuts, vanilla, roasted malt. Taste is quite sweet and very nutty with roasted notes and chocolate in abundance. Mouthfeel is very smooth and extremely velvety with moderate carbonation. Wow.

Tapp. Whats brewing 2016. Svart og oljeaktig konsistens. Lavt karbonert. 
Smaker sjokolade, vanilje, kaff,bourbon,og hassel. En intens og smakfull øl. Vanvittig god
Sample at All in Beer fest 2016. Black with thin tanned head. Milk chocolate, bourbon and light coffee and roasted malt. Semi sweet with low bitterness and low carbonation.

Draft @AllInBeerFest2016. APPEARANCE: pitch-black with a medium brown head. NOSE: strong aroma of bourbon, chocolate, coffee, roasted malt, cookie dough, vanilla, caramel, nuts. TASTE: sweet, long and moderately bitter aftertaste. Well hidden alcohol. MOUTH: full body, with a oily texture. NOTE: fantastic bourbon aroma. Awesome!

Draught at All In Beer Fest 2016, 2016-11-04 Göteborg
AR: dark chocolate, hazenut cream
AP: dark thick brown fluid, wee brownish head
F: thick black chocolate, coffey with milk, hint of hazelnut cream, candis sweetnees - nice one!
